records.addlTxt:
Defendant John W Pulaski in court with attorney William J. Hayes.  Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Atty. Hayes states there is a resolution.

Court recesses the case for the Atty. to fill out the necessary plea paperwork.

Plea Colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 is dismissed and read in.

The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld Sentence of:
(Credit - 1 day) - If revoked

Term of Probation:  12 months

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Complete Anger Management Class;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment.

Costs: $243.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00
 (To be paid as a condition of probation at the rate of $50.00  per month commencing 6-1-15 and/or 45 hours of community service to be completed by end of probation.  Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date.  Failure to pay or complete community service the Court orders 4 days Huber as contempt for non-compliance with Court Order).
